CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 23, 1961, pg. A11 reads: "Girl Friends Committee - When the Pittsburgh Chapter of Girl Friends Inc., entertained its husbands at its annual Christmas party, last Sunday at the Press Club, the above group was in charge. Seated, left to right are Mmes. William Goode, McKinley King, Chester E. Harris (new president), Percy A. Garland (retiring president) and Oscar Harris.  Standing, same order: Mmes, Homer S. Brown, Reginald Dixon, James Henry, Bruce Jackson, (Salem, Ohio), Robert Lavelle, James A. Jordon (chairman) Woody Harris and Wendell Stanton. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Members of the Girl Friends Inc., seated from left: Sara Goode, Ruth King, Ethel Ramos Harris, Hazel Garland, Marjorie Harris; standing: Wilhelmina Byrd Brown, Mrs. Reginald Dixon, Jerri Henry, Mrs. Bruce Jackson, Adah Lavelle, Marion Bond Jordon, Mrs. Woody Harris and Gladys Stanton, posed in Press Club for annual Christmas party
